	<div class="body" id="fhbody-52080095">

		


			<div id="text-52080095" class="p">
			First time accepted submitter szczys writes <i>"Quinn Dunki spent decades developing software before she fabricated her own 6502-based computer. Here she talks about <a href="http://hackaday.com/2013/10/18/guest-rant-from-bits-to-atoms/">crossing between software and hardware (or the other way around)</a> and why this is easier today than it has been in the past."</i>

