	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45176847"><p>OK, more precisely... 30-40MHz also happens to be the point where the demands imposed by a "proper" design ALSO outstrip what you, as an individual, can build with a home-etched 2-layer circuit board, hand solder, and/or troubleshoot when it doesn't work reliably. It's the point where things like 4-layer circuit boards with ground planes and solder masks become non-negotiable requirements. And it's the line in the sand where getting multiple devices to coexist and share that same high-speed bus becomes a RE<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_45176847">

</div>
</div>

