			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_45177057"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45177057"><p>Yes. A board with a ground plane is handy for higher frequency signalling. If you have sufficient cash, you can use one the of hobbyist PCB suppliers to build the PCB for you on a 4 or 6 layer process.</p><p>An alternative for the home hobbyist is to use impedance controlled wires, like twisted pairs or mini coax, terminated correctly. This is more fiddly, but still doable.</p></div>
	</div>

