		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45178871"><p>Remember, this is cache as RAM. The cache IS the memory the firmware is depending on to function. If it gets evicted, you crash. Imagine a program in C. Now, suddenly zero the stack while it's in a function call and see how it performs.</p><p>Meanwhile, the DIMMs are programmed by accessing specific relative locations in memory with the controller set to a special mode. That won't work if other writes get in the way.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_45178871">

