	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45176879"><p>When you develop hardware, you use software simulators, FPGA boards with bit files (a binary representation of the hardware circuits that can be stored on flash memory) and actual silicon. The software simulator is meant to simulate the memory mapping and parallel nature of the hardware, the FPGA boards do this a bit quicker, and actual silicon is the real deal. Only the first two can be updated if things don't work as planned unless the hardware has programmable microcode.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_45176879">

</div>
</div>

