			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_45172869"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45172869"><p>State PE (principle and practice of engineering) exams have had software options since I took them back 23 years ago.  The main thing new is that it used to be an small optional element of the Electrical Engineering discipline, eventually became a larger optional element of the Electrical/Computer Engineering discipline, and now (just starting last year) Software Engineering test is available as it's own discipline.</p><p>The just released pass rate for the new PE-SW test is pretty dismal (~50%) compared to the PE<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

